315static char *
316nsu_strsep(char **stringp, const char *delim) {
317 char *string = *stringp;
318 char *s;
319 const char *d;
320 char sc, dc;
321
322 if (string == NULL)
323 return (NULL);
324
325 for (; *string != '\0'; string++) {
326 sc = *string;
327 for (d = delim; (dc = *d) != '\0'; d++) {
328 if (sc == dc)
329 break;
330 }
331 if (dc == 0)
332 break;
333 }
334
335 for (s = string; *s != '\0'; s++) {
336 sc = *s;
337 for (d = delim; (dc = *d) != '\0'; d++) {
338 if (sc == dc) {
339 *s++ = '\0';
340 *stringp = s;
341 return (string);
342 }
343 }
344 }
345 *stringp = NULL;
346 return (string);
347}

349static void
350reset_system(void) {
351 isc_result_t result;
352
353 ddebug("reset_system()");
354 /* If the update message is still around, destroy it */
355 if (updatemsg != NULL)
356 dns_message_reset(updatemsg, DNS_MESSAGE_INTENTRENDER);
357 else {
358 result = dns_message_create(gmctx, DNS_MESSAGE_INTENTRENDER,
359 &updatemsg);
360 check_result(result, "dns_message_create");
361 }
362 updatemsg->opcode = dns_opcode_update;
363 if (usegsstsig) {
364 if (tsigkey != NULL)
365 dns_tsigkey_detach(&tsigkey);
366 if (gssring != NULL)
367 dns_tsigkeyring_detach(&gssring);
368 tried_other_gsstsig = false;
369 }
370}

372static bool
373parse_hmac(const dns_name_t **hmac, const char *hmacstr, size_t len,
374 uint16_t *digestbitsp)
375{
376 uint16_t digestbits = 0;
377 isc_result_t result;
378 char buf[20];
379
380 REQUIRE(hmac != NULL && *hmac == NULL);
381 REQUIRE(hmacstr != NULL);
382
383 if (len >= sizeof(buf)) {
384 error("unknown key type '%.*s'", (int)(len), hmacstr);
385 return (false);
386 }
387
388 /* Copy len bytes and NUL terminate. */
389 strlcpy(buf, hmacstr, ISC_MIN(len + 1, sizeof(buf)));
390
391 if (strcasecmp(buf, "hmac-md5") == 0) {
392 *hmac = DNS_TSIG_HMACMD5_NAME;
393 } else if (strncasecmp(buf, "hmac-md5-", 9) == 0) {
394 *hmac = DNS_TSIG_HMACMD5_NAME;
395 result = isc_parse_uint16(&digestbits, &buf[9], 10);
396 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS || digestbits > 128) {
397 error("digest-bits out of range [0..128]");
398 return (false);
399 }
400 *digestbitsp = (digestbits + 7) & ~0x7U;
401 } else if (strcasecmp(buf, "hmac-sha1") == 0) {
402 *hmac = DNS_TSIG_HMACSHA1_NAME;
403 } else if (strncasecmp(buf, "hmac-sha1-", 10) == 0) {
404 *hmac = DNS_TSIG_HMACSHA1_NAME;
405 result = isc_parse_uint16(&digestbits, &buf[10], 10);
406 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS || digestbits > 160) {
407 error("digest-bits out of range [0..160]");
408 return (false);
409 }
410 *digestbitsp = (digestbits + 7) & ~0x7U;
411 } else if (strcasecmp(buf, "hmac-sha224") == 0) {
412 *hmac = DNS_TSIG_HMACSHA224_NAME;
413 } else if (strncasecmp(buf, "hmac-sha224-", 12) == 0) {
414 *hmac = DNS_TSIG_HMACSHA224_NAME;
415 result = isc_parse_uint16(&digestbits, &buf[12], 10);
416 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS || digestbits > 224) {
417 error("digest-bits out of range [0..224]");
418 return (false);
419 }
420 *digestbitsp = (digestbits + 7) & ~0x7U;
421 } else if (strcasecmp(buf, "hmac-sha256") == 0) {
422 *hmac = DNS_TSIG_HMACSHA256_NAME;
423 } else if (strncasecmp(buf, "hmac-sha256-", 12) == 0) {
424 *hmac = DNS_TSIG_HMACSHA256_NAME;
425 result = isc_parse_uint16(&digestbits, &buf[12], 10);
426 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS || digestbits > 256) {
427 error("digest-bits out of range [0..256]");
428 return (false);
429 }
430 *digestbitsp = (digestbits + 7) & ~0x7U;
431 } else if (strcasecmp(buf, "hmac-sha384") == 0) {
432 *hmac = DNS_TSIG_HMACSHA384_NAME;
433 } else if (strncasecmp(buf, "hmac-sha384-", 12) == 0) {
434 *hmac = DNS_TSIG_HMACSHA384_NAME;
435 result = isc_parse_uint16(&digestbits, &buf[12], 10);
436 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS || digestbits > 384) {
437 error("digest-bits out of range [0..384]");
438 return (false);
439 }
440 *digestbitsp = (digestbits + 7) & ~0x7U;
441 } else if (strcasecmp(buf, "hmac-sha512") == 0) {
442 *hmac = DNS_TSIG_HMACSHA512_NAME;
443 } else if (strncasecmp(buf, "hmac-sha512-", 12) == 0) {
444 *hmac = DNS_TSIG_HMACSHA512_NAME;
445 result = isc_parse_uint16(&digestbits, &buf[12], 10);
446 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS || digestbits > 512) {
447 error("digest-bits out of range [0..512]");
448 return (false);
449 }
450 *digestbitsp = (digestbits + 7) & ~0x7U;
451 } else {
452 error("unknown key type '%s'", buf);
453 return (false);
454 }
455 return (true);
456}

458static int
459basenamelen(const char *file) {
460 int len = strlen(file);
461
462 if (len > 1 && file[len - 1] == '.')
463 len -= 1;
464 else if (len > 8 && strcmp(file + len - 8, ".private") == 0)
465 len -= 8;
466 else if (len > 4 && strcmp(file + len - 4, ".key") == 0)
467 len -= 4;
468 return (len);
469}

471static void
472setup_keystr(void) {
473 unsigned char *secret = NULL;
474 int secretlen;
475 isc_buffer_t secretbuf;
476 isc_result_t result;
477 isc_buffer_t keynamesrc;
478 char *secretstr;
479 char *s, *n;
480 dns_fixedname_t fkeyname;
481 dns_name_t *mykeyname;
482 char *name;
483 const dns_name_t *hmacname = NULL;
484 uint16_t digestbits = 0;
485
486 mykeyname = dns_fixedname_initname(&fkeyname);
487
488 debug("Creating key...");
489
490 s = strchr(keystr, ':');
491 if (s == NULL || s == keystr || s[1] == 0)
492 fatal("key option must specify [hmac:]keyname:secret");
493 secretstr = s + 1;
494 n = strchr(secretstr, ':');
495 if (n != NULL) {
496 if (n == secretstr || n[1] == 0)
497 fatal("key option must specify [hmac:]keyname:secret");
498 name = secretstr;
499 secretstr = n + 1;
500 if (!parse_hmac(&hmacname, keystr, s - keystr, &digestbits)) {
501 exit(1);
502 }
503 } else {
504 hmacname = DNS_TSIG_HMACMD5_NAME;
505 name = keystr;
506 n = s;
507 }
508
509 isc_buffer_init(&keynamesrc, name, (unsigned int)(n - name));
510 isc_buffer_add(&keynamesrc, (unsigned int)(n - name));
511
512 debug("namefromtext");
513 result = dns_name_fromtext(mykeyname, &keynamesrc, dns_rootname, 0,
514 NULL);
515 check_result(result, "dns_name_fromtext");
516
517 secretlen = strlen(secretstr) * 3 / 4;
518 secret = isc_mem_allocate(gmctx, secretlen);
519 if (secret == NULL)
520 fatal("out of memory");
521
522 isc_buffer_init(&secretbuf, secret, secretlen);
523 result = isc_base64_decodestring(secretstr, &secretbuf);
524 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
525 fprintf(stderr, "could not create key from %s: %s\n",
526 keystr, isc_result_totext(result));
527 goto failure;
528 }
529
530 secretlen = isc_buffer_usedlength(&secretbuf);
531
532 debug("keycreate");
533 result = dns_tsigkey_create(mykeyname, hmacname, secret, secretlen,
534 false, NULL, 0, 0, gmctx, NULL,
535 &tsigkey);
536 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
537 fprintf(stderr, "could not create key from %s: %s\n",
538 keystr, dns_result_totext(result));
539 else
540 dst_key_setbits(tsigkey->key, digestbits);
541 failure:
542 if (secret != NULL)
543 isc_mem_free(gmctx, secret);
544}

546/*
547 * Get a key from a named.conf format keyfile
548 */
549static isc_result_t
550read_sessionkey(isc_mem_t *mctx, isc_log_t *lctx) {
551 cfg_parser_t *pctx = NULL;
552 cfg_obj_t *sessionkey = NULL;
553 const cfg_obj_t *key = NULL;
554 const cfg_obj_t *secretobj = NULL;
555 const cfg_obj_t *algorithmobj = NULL;
556 const char *mykeyname;
557 const char *secretstr;
558 const char *algorithm;
559 isc_result_t result;
560 int len;
561
562 if (! isc_file_exists(keyfile))
563 return (ISC_R_FILENOTFOUND);
564
565 result = cfg_parser_create(mctx, lctx, &pctx);
566 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
567 goto cleanup;
568
569 result = cfg_parse_file(pctx, keyfile, &cfg_type_sessionkey,
570 &sessionkey);
571 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
572 goto cleanup;
573
574 result = cfg_map_get(sessionkey, "key", &key);
575 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
576 goto cleanup;
577
578 (void) cfg_map_get(key, "secret", &secretobj);
579 (void) cfg_map_get(key, "algorithm", &algorithmobj);
580 if (secretobj == NULL || algorithmobj == NULL)
581 fatal("key must have algorithm and secret");
582
583 mykeyname = cfg_obj_asstring(cfg_map_getname(key));
584 secretstr = cfg_obj_asstring(secretobj);
585 algorithm = cfg_obj_asstring(algorithmobj);
586
587 len = strlen(algorithm) + strlen(mykeyname) + strlen(secretstr) + 3;
588 keystr = isc_mem_allocate(mctx, len);
589 if (keystr == NULL)
590 fatal("out of memory");
591 snprintf(keystr, len, "%s:%s:%s", algorithm, mykeyname, secretstr);
592 setup_keystr();
593
594 cleanup:
595 if (pctx != NULL) {
596 if (sessionkey != NULL)
597 cfg_obj_destroy(pctx, &sessionkey);
598 cfg_parser_destroy(&pctx);
599 }
600
601 if (keystr != NULL)
602 isc_mem_free(mctx, keystr);
603
604 return (result);
605}

607static void
608setup_keyfile(isc_mem_t *mctx, isc_log_t *lctx) {
609 dst_key_t *dstkey = NULL;
610 isc_result_t result;
611 const dns_name_t *hmacname = NULL;
612
613 debug("Creating key...");
614
615 if (sig0key != NULL)
616 dst_key_free(&sig0key);
617
618 /* Try reading the key from a K* pair */
619 result = dst_key_fromnamedfile(keyfile, NULL,
620 DST_TYPE_PRIVATE | DST_TYPE_KEY, mctx,
621 &dstkey);
622
623 /* If that didn't work, try reading it as a session.key keyfile */
624 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
625 result = read_sessionkey(mctx, lctx);
626 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS)
627 return;
628 }
629
630 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
631 fprintf(stderr, "could not read key from %.*s.{private,key}: "
632 "%s\n", basenamelen(keyfile), keyfile,
633 isc_result_totext(result));
634 return;
635 }
636
637 switch (dst_key_alg(dstkey)) {
638 case DST_ALG_HMACMD5:
639 hmacname = DNS_TSIG_HMACMD5_NAME;
640 break;
641 case DST_ALG_HMACSHA1:
642 hmacname = DNS_TSIG_HMACSHA1_NAME;
643 break;
644 case DST_ALG_HMACSHA224:
645 hmacname = DNS_TSIG_HMACSHA224_NAME;
646 break;
647 case DST_ALG_HMACSHA256:
648 hmacname = DNS_TSIG_HMACSHA256_NAME;
649 break;
650 case DST_ALG_HMACSHA384:
651 hmacname = DNS_TSIG_HMACSHA384_NAME;
652 break;
653 case DST_ALG_HMACSHA512:
654 hmacname = DNS_TSIG_HMACSHA512_NAME;
655 break;
656 }
657 if (hmacname != NULL) {
658 result = dns_tsigkey_createfromkey(dst_key_name(dstkey),
659 hmacname, dstkey, false,
660 NULL, 0, 0, mctx, NULL,
661 &tsigkey);
662 dst_key_free(&dstkey);
663 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
664 fprintf(stderr, "could not create key from %s: %s\n",
665 keyfile, isc_result_totext(result));
666 return;
667 }
668 } else {
669 dst_key_attach(dstkey, &sig0key);
670 dst_key_free(&dstkey);
671 }
672}

674static void
675doshutdown(void) {
676 isc_task_detach(&global_task);
677
678 /*
679 * The isc_mem_put of master_servers must be before the
680 * isc_mem_put of servers as it sets the servers pointer
681 * to NULL.
682 */
683 if (master_servers != NULL && master_servers != servers)
684 isc_mem_put(gmctx, master_servers,
685 master_alloc * sizeof(isc_sockaddr_t));
686
687 if (servers != NULL)
688 isc_mem_put(gmctx, servers, ns_alloc * sizeof(isc_sockaddr_t));
689
690 if (localaddr4 != NULL)
691 isc_mem_put(gmctx, localaddr4, sizeof(isc_sockaddr_t));
692
693 if (localaddr6 != NULL)
694 isc_mem_put(gmctx, localaddr6, sizeof(isc_sockaddr_t));
695
696 if (tsigkey != NULL) {
697 ddebug("Freeing TSIG key");
698 dns_tsigkey_detach(&tsigkey);
699 }
700
701 if (sig0key != NULL) {
702 ddebug("Freeing SIG(0) key");
703 dst_key_free(&sig0key);
704 }
705
706 if (updatemsg != NULL)
707 dns_message_destroy(&updatemsg);
708
709 if (is_dst_up) {
710 ddebug("Destroy DST lib");
711 dst_lib_destroy();
712 is_dst_up = false;
713 }
714
715 ddebug("Destroying request manager");
716 dns_requestmgr_detach(&requestmgr);
717
718 ddebug("Freeing the dispatchers");
719 if (have_ipv4)
720 dns_dispatch_detach(&dispatchv4);
721 if (have_ipv6)
722 dns_dispatch_detach(&dispatchv6);
723
724 ddebug("Shutting down dispatch manager");
725 dns_dispatchmgr_destroy(&dispatchmgr);
726
727}

731 ddebug("Shutting down request manager");
732 dns_requestmgr_shutdown(requestmgr);
733
734 if (requests != 0)

736
737 doshutdown();

752/*
753 * Try honoring the operating system's preferred ephemeral port range.
754 */
755static void
756set_source_ports(dns_dispatchmgr_t *manager) {
757 isc_portset_t *v4portset = NULL, *v6portset = NULL;
758 in_port_t udpport_low, udpport_high;
759 isc_result_t result;
760
761 result = isc_portset_create(gmctx, &v4portset);
762 check_result(result, "isc_portset_create (v4)");
763 result = isc_net_getudpportrange(AF_INET, &udpport_low, &udpport_high);
764 check_result(result, "isc_net_getudpportrange (v4)");
765 isc_portset_addrange(v4portset, udpport_low, udpport_high);
766
767 result = isc_portset_create(gmctx, &v6portset);
768 check_result(result, "isc_portset_create (v6)");

770 check_result(result, "isc_net_getudpportrange (v6)");
771 isc_portset_addrange(v6portset, udpport_low, udpport_high);
772
773 result = dns_dispatchmgr_setavailports(manager, v4portset, v6portset);
774 check_result(result, "dns_dispatchmgr_setavailports");
775
776 isc_portset_destroy(gmctx, &v4portset);
777 isc_portset_destroy(gmctx, &v6portset);
778}

780static void
781setup_system(void) {
782 isc_result_t result;
783 isc_sockaddr_t bind_any, bind_any6;
784 unsigned int attrs, attrmask;
785 isc_sockaddrlist_t *nslist;
786 isc_logconfig_t *logconfig = NULL;
787 irs_resconf_t *resconf = NULL;
788
789 ddebug("setup_system()");
790
791 dns_result_register();
792
793 result = isc_log_create(gmctx, &glctx, &logconfig);
794 check_result(result, "isc_log_create");
795
796 isc_log_setcontext(glctx);
797 dns_log_init(glctx);
798 dns_log_setcontext(glctx);
799
800 result = isc_log_usechannel(logconfig, "default_debug", NULL, NULL);
801 check_result(result, "isc_log_usechannel");
802
803 isc_log_setdebuglevel(glctx, logdebuglevel);
804
805 result = irs_resconf_load(gmctx, RESOLV_CONF, &resconf);
806 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS && result != ISC_R_FILENOTFOUND) {
807 fatal("parse of %s failed", RESOLV_CONF);
808 }
809
810 nslist = irs_resconf_getnameservers(resconf);
811
812 if (servers != NULL) {
813 if (master_servers == servers)
814 master_servers = NULL;
815 isc_mem_put(gmctx, servers, ns_alloc * sizeof(isc_sockaddr_t));
816 }
817
818 ns_inuse = 0;
819 if (local_only || ISC_LIST_EMPTY(*nslist)) {
820 struct in_addr in;
821 struct in6_addr in6;
822
823 if (local_only && keyfile == NULL)
824 keyfile = SESSION_KEYFILE;
825
826 default_servers = !local_only;
827
828 ns_total = ns_alloc = (have_ipv4 ? 1 : 0) + (have_ipv6 ? 1 : 0);
829 servers = isc_mem_get(gmctx, ns_alloc * sizeof(isc_sockaddr_t));
830 if (servers == NULL)
831 fatal("out of memory");
832
833 if (have_ipv6) {
834 memset(&in6, 0, sizeof(in6));
835 in6.s6_addr[15] = 1;
836 isc_sockaddr_fromin6(&servers[0], &in6, dnsport);
837 }
838 if (have_ipv4) {
839 in.s_addr = htonl(INADDR_LOOPBACK);
840 isc_sockaddr_fromin(&servers[(have_ipv6 ? 1 : 0)],
841 &in, dnsport);
842 }
843 } else {
844 isc_sockaddr_t *sa;
845 int i;
846
847 /*
848 * Count the nameservers (skipping any that we can't use
849 * because of address family restrictions) and allocate
850 * the servers array.
851 */
852 ns_total = 0;
853 for (sa = ISC_LIST_HEAD(*nslist);
854 sa != NULL;
855 sa = ISC_LIST_NEXT(sa, link))
856 {
857 switch (sa->type.sa.sa_family) {
858 case AF_INET:
859 if (have_ipv4) {
860 ns_total++;
861 }
862 break;
863 case AF_INET6:
864 if (have_ipv6) {
865 ns_total++;
866 }
867 break;
868 default:
869 fatal("bad family");
870 }
871 }
872
873 ns_alloc = ns_total;
874 servers = isc_mem_get(gmctx, ns_alloc * sizeof(isc_sockaddr_t));
875 if (servers == NULL)
876 fatal("out of memory");
877
878 i = 0;
879 for (sa = ISC_LIST_HEAD(*nslist);
880 sa != NULL;
881 sa = ISC_LIST_NEXT(sa, link))
882 {
883 switch (sa->type.sa.sa_family) {
884 case AF_INET:
885 if (have_ipv4) {
886 sa->type.sin.sin_port = htons(dnsport);
887 } else {
888 continue;
889 }
890 break;
891 case AF_INET6:
892 if (have_ipv6) {
893 sa->type.sin6.sin6_port = htons(dnsport);
894 } else {
895 continue;
896 }
897 break;
898 default:
899 fatal("bad family");
900 }
901 INSIST(i < ns_alloc);
902 servers[i++] = *sa;
903 }
904 }
905
906 irs_resconf_destroy(&resconf);
907
908 result = dns_dispatchmgr_create(gmctx, &dispatchmgr);
909 check_result(result, "dns_dispatchmgr_create");
910
911 result = isc_socketmgr_create(gmctx, &socketmgr);
912 check_result(result, "dns_socketmgr_create");
913
914 result = isc_timermgr_create(gmctx, &timermgr);
915 check_result(result, "dns_timermgr_create");
916
917 result = isc_taskmgr_create(gmctx, 1, 0, &taskmgr);
918 check_result(result, "isc_taskmgr_create");
919
920 result = isc_task_create(taskmgr, 0, &global_task);
921 check_result(result, "isc_task_create");
922
923 result = isc_task_onshutdown(global_task, shutdown_program, NULL);
924 check_result(result, "isc_task_onshutdown");
925
926 result = dst_lib_init(gmctx, NULL);
927 check_result(result, "dst_lib_init");
928 is_dst_up = true;
929
930 set_source_ports(dispatchmgr);
931
932 attrmask = DNS_DISPATCHATTR_UDP | DNS_DISPATCHATTR_TCP;
933 attrmask |= DNS_DISPATCHATTR_IPV4 | DNS_DISPATCHATTR_IPV6;
934
935 if (have_ipv6) {
936 attrs = DNS_DISPATCHATTR_UDP;
937 attrs |= DNS_DISPATCHATTR_MAKEQUERY;
938 attrs |= DNS_DISPATCHATTR_IPV6;
939 isc_sockaddr_any6(&bind_any6);
940 result = dns_dispatch_getudp(dispatchmgr, socketmgr, taskmgr,
941 &bind_any6, PACKETSIZE,
942 4, 2, 3, 5,
943 attrs, attrmask, &dispatchv6);
944 check_result(result, "dns_dispatch_getudp (v6)");
945 }
946
947 if (have_ipv4) {
948 attrs = DNS_DISPATCHATTR_UDP;
949 attrs |= DNS_DISPATCHATTR_MAKEQUERY;
950 attrs |= DNS_DISPATCHATTR_IPV4;
951 isc_sockaddr_any(&bind_any);
952 result = dns_dispatch_getudp(dispatchmgr, socketmgr, taskmgr,
953 &bind_any, PACKETSIZE,
954 4, 2, 3, 5,
955 attrs, attrmask, &dispatchv4);
956 check_result(result, "dns_dispatch_getudp (v4)");
957 }
958
959 result = dns_requestmgr_create(gmctx, timermgr,
960 socketmgr, taskmgr, dispatchmgr,
961 dispatchv4, dispatchv6, &requestmgr);
962 check_result(result, "dns_requestmgr_create");
963
964 if (keystr != NULL)
965 setup_keystr();
966 else if (local_only) {
967 result = read_sessionkey(gmctx, glctx);
968 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
969 fatal("can't read key from %s: %s\n",
970 keyfile, isc_result_totext(result));
971 } else if (keyfile != NULL)
972 setup_keyfile(gmctx, glctx);
973}

996#define PARSE_ARGS_FMT "46dDML:y:ghilovk:p:Pr:R::t:Tu:V"
997
998static void
999pre_parse_args(int argc, char **argv) {
1000 dns_rdatatype_t t;
1001 int ch;
1002 char buf[100];
1003 bool doexit = false;
1004 bool ipv4only = false, ipv6only = false;
1005
1006 while ((ch = isc_commandline_parse(argc, argv, PARSE_ARGS_FMT)) != -1) {
1007 switch (ch) {
1008 case 'M': /* was -dm */
1009 debugging = true;
1010 ddebugging = true;
1011 memdebugging = true;
1012 isc_mem_debugging = ISC_MEM_DEBUGTRACE |
1013 ISC_MEM_DEBUGRECORD;
1014 break;
1015
1016 case '4':
1017 if (ipv6only) {
1018 fatal("only one of -4 and -6 allowed");
1019 }
1020 ipv4only = true;
1021 break;
1022
1023 case '6':
1024 if (ipv4only) {
1025 fatal("only one of -4 and -6 allowed");
1026 }
1027 ipv6only = true;
1028 break;
1029
1030 case '?':
1031 case 'h':
1032 if (isc_commandline_option != '?')
1033 fprintf(stderr, "%s: invalid argument -%c\n",
1034 argv[0], isc_commandline_option);
1035 fprintf(stderr, "usage: nsupdate [-dDi] [-L level] [-l]"
1036 "[-g | -o | -y keyname:secret | -k keyfile] "
1037 "[-v] [-V] [-P] [-T] [-4 | -6] [filename]\n");
1038 exit(1);
1039
1040 case 'P':
1041 for (t = 0xff00; t <= 0xfffe; t++) {
1042 if (dns_rdatatype_ismeta(t))
1043 continue;
1044 dns_rdatatype_format(t, buf, sizeof(buf));
1045 if (strncmp(buf, "TYPE", 4) != 0)
1046 fprintf(stdout, "%s\n", buf);
1047 }
1048 doexit = true;
1049 break;
1050
1051 case 'T':
1052 for (t = 1; t <= 0xfeff; t++) {
1053 if (dns_rdatatype_ismeta(t))
1054 continue;
1055 dns_rdatatype_format(t, buf, sizeof(buf));
1056 if (strncmp(buf, "TYPE", 4) != 0)
1057 fprintf(stdout, "%s\n", buf);
1058 }
1059 doexit = true;
1060 break;
1061
1062 case 'V':
1063 version();
1064 doexit = true;
1065 break;
1066
1067 default:
1068 break;
1069 }
1070 }
1071 if (doexit)
1072 exit(0);
1073 isc_commandline_reset = true;
1074 isc_commandline_index = 1;
1075}
1076
1077static void
1078parse_args(int argc, char **argv) {
1079 int ch;
1080 uint32_t i;
1081 isc_result_t result;
1082 bool force_interactive = false;
1083
1084 debug("parse_args");
1085 while ((ch = isc_commandline_parse(argc, argv, PARSE_ARGS_FMT)) != -1) {
1086 switch (ch) {
1087 case '4':
1088 if (have_ipv4) {
1089 isc_net_disableipv6();
1090 have_ipv6 = false;
1091 } else {
1092 fatal("can't find IPv4 networking");
1093 }
1094 break;
1095 case '6':
1096 if (have_ipv6) {
1097 isc_net_disableipv4();
1098 have_ipv4 = false;
1099 } else {
1100 fatal("can't find IPv6 networking");
1101 }
1102 break;
1103 case 'd':
1104 debugging = true;
1105 break;
1106 case 'D': /* was -dd */
1107 debugging = true;
1108 ddebugging = true;
1109 break;
1110 case 'M':
1111 break;
1112 case 'i':
1113 force_interactive = true;
1114 interactive = true;
1115 break;
1116 case 'l':
1117 local_only = true;
1118 break;
1119 case 'L':
1120 result = isc_parse_uint32(&i, isc_commandline_argument,
1121 10);
1122 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
1123 fprintf(stderr, "bad library debug value "
1124 "'%s'\n", isc_commandline_argument);
1125 exit(1);
1126 }
1127 logdebuglevel = i;
1128 break;
1129 case 'y':
1130 keystr = isc_commandline_argument;
1131 break;
1132 case 'v':
1133 usevc = true;
1134 break;
1135 case 'k':
1136 keyfile = isc_commandline_argument;
1137 break;
1138 case 'g':
1139 usegsstsig = true;
1140 use_win2k_gsstsig = false;
1141 break;
1142 case 'o':
1143 usegsstsig = true;
1144 use_win2k_gsstsig = true;
1145 break;
1146 case 'p':
1147 result = isc_parse_uint16(&dnsport,
1148 isc_commandline_argument, 10);
1149 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
1150 fprintf(stderr, "bad port number "
1151 "'%s'\n", isc_commandline_argument);
1152 exit(1);
1153 }
1154 break;
1155 case 't':
1156 result = isc_parse_uint32(&timeout,
1157 isc_commandline_argument, 10);
1158 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
1159 fprintf(stderr, "bad timeout '%s'\n", isc_commandline_argument);
1160 exit(1);
1161 }
1162 if (timeout == 0)
1163 timeout = UINT_MAX;
1164 break;
1165 case 'u':
1166 result = isc_parse_uint32(&udp_timeout,
1167 isc_commandline_argument, 10);
1168 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
1169 fprintf(stderr, "bad udp timeout '%s'\n", isc_commandline_argument);
1170 exit(1);
1171 }
1172 if (udp_timeout == 0)
1173 udp_timeout = UINT_MAX;
1174 break;
1175 case 'r':
1176 result = isc_parse_uint32(&udp_retries,
1177 isc_commandline_argument, 10);
1178 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
1179 fprintf(stderr, "bad udp retries '%s'\n", isc_commandline_argument);
1180 exit(1);
1181 }
1182 break;
1183
1184 case 'R':
1185 fatal("The -R options has been deprecated.\n");
1186 break;
1187
1188 default:
1189 fprintf(stderr, "%s: unhandled option: %c\n",
1190 argv[0], isc_commandline_option);
1191 exit(1);
1192 }
1193 }
1194 if (keyfile != NULL && keystr != NULL) {
1195 fprintf(stderr, "%s: cannot specify both -k and -y\n",
1196 argv[0]);
1197 exit(1);
1198 }
1199
1200#ifdef GSSAPI
1201 if (usegsstsig && (keyfile != NULL || keystr != NULL)) {
1202 fprintf(stderr, "%s: cannot specify -g with -k or -y\n",
1203 argv[0]);
1204 exit(1);
1205 }
1206#else
1207 if (usegsstsig) {
1208 fprintf(stderr, "%s: cannot specify -g or -o, " \
1209 "program not linked with GSS API Library\n",
1210 argv[0]);
1211 exit(1);
1212 }
1213#endif
1214
1215 if (argv[isc_commandline_index] != NULL) {
1216 if (strcmp(argv[isc_commandline_index], "-") == 0) {
1217 input = stdin;
1218 } else {
1219 result = isc_stdio_open(argv[isc_commandline_index],
1220 "r", &input);
1221 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
1222 fprintf(stderr, "could not open '%s': %s\n",
1223 argv[isc_commandline_index],
1224 isc_result_totext(result));
1225 exit(1);
1226 }
1227 }
1228 if (!force_interactive) {
1229 interactive = false;
1230 }
1231 }
1232}

1234static uint16_t
1235parse_name(char **cmdlinep, dns_message_t *msg, dns_name_t **namep) {
1236 isc_result_t result;
1237 char *word;
1238 isc_buffer_t *namebuf = NULL;
1239 isc_buffer_t source;
1240
1241 word = nsu_strsep(cmdlinep, " \t\r\n");
1242 if (word == NULL || *word == 0) {
1243 fprintf(stderr, "could not read owner name\n");
1244 return (STATUS_SYNTAX);
1245 }
1246
1247 result = dns_message_gettempname(msg, namep);
1248 check_result(result, "dns_message_gettempname");
1249 result = isc_buffer_allocate(gmctx, &namebuf, DNS_NAME_MAXWIRE);
1250 check_result(result, "isc_buffer_allocate");
1251 dns_name_init(*namep, NULL);
1252 dns_name_setbuffer(*namep, namebuf);
1253 dns_message_takebuffer(msg, &namebuf);
1254 isc_buffer_init(&source, word, strlen(word));
1255 isc_buffer_add(&source, strlen(word));
1256 result = dns_name_fromtext(*namep, &source, dns_rootname, 0, NULL);
1257 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
1258 error("invalid owner name: %s", isc_result_totext(result));
1259 isc_buffer_invalidate(&source);
1260 dns_message_puttempname(msg, namep);
1261 return (STATUS_SYNTAX);
1262 }
1263 isc_buffer_invalidate(&source);
1264 return (STATUS_MORE);
1265}
1266
1267static uint16_t
1268parse_rdata(char **cmdlinep, dns_rdataclass_t rdataclass,
1269 dns_rdatatype_t rdatatype, dns_message_t *msg,
1270 dns_rdata_t *rdata)
1271{
1272 char *cmdline = *cmdlinep;
1273 isc_buffer_t source, *buf = NULL, *newbuf = NULL;
1274 isc_region_t r;
1275 isc_lex_t *lex = NULL;
1276 dns_rdatacallbacks_t callbacks;
1277 isc_result_t result;
1278
1279 if (cmdline == NULL) {
1280 rdata->flags = DNS_RDATA_UPDATE;
1281 return (STATUS_MORE);
1282 }
1283
1284 while (*cmdline != 0 && isspace((unsigned char)*cmdline))
1285 cmdline++;
1286
1287 if (*cmdline != 0) {
1288 dns_rdatacallbacks_init(&callbacks);
1289 result = isc_lex_create(gmctx, strlen(cmdline), &lex);
1290 check_result(result, "isc_lex_create");
1291 isc_buffer_init(&source, cmdline, strlen(cmdline));
1292 isc_buffer_add(&source, strlen(cmdline));
1293 result = isc_lex_openbuffer(lex, &source);
1294 check_result(result, "isc_lex_openbuffer");
1295 result = isc_buffer_allocate(gmctx, &buf, MAXWIRE);
1296 check_result(result, "isc_buffer_allocate");
1297 result = dns_rdata_fromtext(NULL, rdataclass, rdatatype, lex,
1298 dns_rootname, 0, gmctx, buf,
1299 &callbacks);
1300 isc_lex_destroy(&lex);
1301 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
1302 isc_buffer_usedregion(buf, &r);
1303 result = isc_buffer_allocate(gmctx, &newbuf, r.length);
1304 check_result(result, "isc_buffer_allocate");
1305 isc_buffer_putmem(newbuf, r.base, r.length);
1306 isc_buffer_usedregion(newbuf, &r);
1307 dns_rdata_fromregion(rdata, rdataclass, rdatatype, &r);
1308 isc_buffer_free(&buf);
1309 dns_message_takebuffer(msg, &newbuf);
1310 } else {
1311 fprintf(stderr, "invalid rdata format: %s\n",
1312 isc_result_totext(result));
1313 isc_buffer_free(&buf);
1314 return (STATUS_SYNTAX);
1315 }
1316 } else {
1317 rdata->flags = DNS_RDATA_UPDATE;
1318 }
1319 *cmdlinep = cmdline;
1320 return (STATUS_MORE);
1321}

1323static uint16_t
1324make_prereq(char *cmdline, bool ispositive, bool isrrset) {
1325 isc_result_t result;
1326 char *word;
1327 dns_name_t *name = NULL;
1328 isc_textregion_t region;
1329 dns_rdataset_t *rdataset = NULL;
1330 dns_rdatalist_t *rdatalist = NULL;
1331 dns_rdataclass_t rdataclass;
1332 dns_rdatatype_t rdatatype;
1333 dns_rdata_t *rdata = NULL;
1334 uint16_t retval;
1335
1336 ddebug("make_prereq()");
1337
1338 /*
1339 * Read the owner name
1340 */
1341 retval = parse_name(&cmdline, updatemsg, &name);
1342 if (retval != STATUS_MORE)
1343 return (retval);
1344
1345 /*
1346 * If this is an rrset prereq, read the class or type.
1347 */
1348 if (isrrset) {
1349 word = nsu_strsep(&cmdline, " \t\r\n");
1350 if (word == NULL || *word == 0) {
1351 fprintf(stderr, "could not read class or type\n");
1352 goto failure;
1353 }
1354 region.base = word;
1355 region.length = strlen(word);
1356 result = dns_rdataclass_fromtext(&rdataclass, &region);
1357 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
1358 if (!setzoneclass(rdataclass)) {
1359 fprintf(stderr, "class mismatch: %s\n", word);
1360 goto failure;
1361 }
1362 /*
1363 * Now read the type.
1364 */
1365 word = nsu_strsep(&cmdline, " \t\r\n");
1366 if (word == NULL || *word == 0) {
1367 fprintf(stderr, "could not read type\n");
1368 goto failure;
1369 }
1370 region.base = word;
1371 region.length = strlen(word);
1372 result = dns_rdatatype_fromtext(&rdatatype, &region);
1373 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
1374 fprintf(stderr, "invalid type: %s\n", word);
1375 goto failure;
1376 }
1377 } else {
1378 rdataclass = getzoneclass();
1379 result = dns_rdatatype_fromtext(&rdatatype, &region);
1380 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
1381 fprintf(stderr, "invalid type: %s\n", word);
1382 goto failure;
1383 }
1384 }
1385 } else
1386 rdatatype = dns_rdatatype_any;
1387
1388 result = dns_message_gettemprdata(updatemsg, &rdata);
1389 check_result(result, "dns_message_gettemprdata");
1390
1391 dns_rdata_init(rdata);
1392
1393 if (isrrset && ispositive) {
1394 retval = parse_rdata(&cmdline, rdataclass, rdatatype,
1395 updatemsg, rdata);
1396 if (retval != STATUS_MORE)
1397 goto failure;
1398 } else
1399 rdata->flags = DNS_RDATA_UPDATE;
1400
1401 result = dns_message_gettemprdatalist(updatemsg, &rdatalist);
1402 check_result(result, "dns_message_gettemprdatalist");
1403 result = dns_message_gettemprdataset(updatemsg, &rdataset);
1404 check_result(result, "dns_message_gettemprdataset");
1405 rdatalist->type = rdatatype;
1406 if (ispositive) {
1407 if (isrrset && rdata->data != NULL)
1408 rdatalist->rdclass = rdataclass;
1409 else
1410 rdatalist->rdclass = dns_rdataclass_any;
1411 } else
1412 rdatalist->rdclass = dns_rdataclass_none;
1413 rdata->rdclass = rdatalist->rdclass;
1414 rdata->type = rdatatype;
1415 ISC_LIST_APPEND(rdatalist->rdata, rdata, link);
1416 dns_rdatalist_tordataset(rdatalist, rdataset);
1417 ISC_LIST_INIT(name->list);
1418 ISC_LIST_APPEND(name->list, rdataset, link);
1419 dns_message_addname(updatemsg, name, DNS_SECTION_PREREQUISITE);
1420 return (STATUS_MORE);
1421
1422 failure:
1423 if (name != NULL)
1424 dns_message_puttempname(updatemsg, &name);
1425 return (STATUS_SYNTAX);
1426}

1458static uint16_t
1459evaluate_server(char *cmdline) {
1460 char *word, *server;
1461 long port;
1462
1463 if (local_only) {
1464 fprintf(stderr, "cannot reset server in localhost-only mode\n");
1465 return (STATUS_SYNTAX);
1466 }
1467
1468 word = nsu_strsep(&cmdline, " \t\r\n");
1469 if (word == NULL || *word == 0) {
1470 fprintf(stderr, "could not read server name\n");
1471 return (STATUS_SYNTAX);
1472 }
1473 server = word;
1474
1475 word = nsu_strsep(&cmdline, " \t\r\n");
1476 if (word == NULL || *word == 0)
1477 port = dnsport;
1478 else {
1479 char *endp;
1480 port = strtol(word, &endp, 10);
1481 if (*endp != 0) {
1482 fprintf(stderr, "port '%s' is not numeric\n", word);
1483 return (STATUS_SYNTAX);
1484 } else if (port < 1 || port > 65535) {
1485 fprintf(stderr, "port '%s' is out of range "
1486 "(1 to 65535)\n", word);
1487 return (STATUS_SYNTAX);
1488 }
1489 }
1490
1491 if (servers != NULL) {
1492 if (master_servers == servers)
1493 master_servers = NULL;
1494 isc_mem_put(gmctx, servers, ns_alloc * sizeof(isc_sockaddr_t));
1495 }
1496
1497 default_servers = false;
1498
1499 ns_alloc = MAX_SERVERADDRS;
1500 ns_inuse = 0;
1501 servers = isc_mem_get(gmctx, ns_alloc * sizeof(isc_sockaddr_t));
1502 if (servers == NULL)
1503 fatal("out of memory");
1504
1505 memset(servers, 0, ns_alloc * sizeof(isc_sockaddr_t));
1506 ns_total = get_addresses(server, (in_port_t)port, servers, ns_alloc);
1507 if (ns_total == 0) {
1508 return (STATUS_SYNTAX);
1509 }
1510
1511 return (STATUS_MORE);
1512}

1518 struct in_addr in4;

1527
1528 word = nsu_strsep(&cmdline, " \t\r\n");

1559 }
1560
1561 return (STATUS_MORE);

1564static uint16_t
1565evaluate_key(char *cmdline) {
1566 char *namestr;
1567 char *secretstr;
1568 isc_buffer_t b;
1569 isc_result_t result;
1570 dns_fixedname_t fkeyname;
1571 dns_name_t *mykeyname;
1572 int secretlen;
1573 unsigned char *secret = NULL;
1574 isc_buffer_t secretbuf;
1575 const dns_name_t *hmacname = NULL;
1576 uint16_t digestbits = 0;
1577 char *n;
1578
1579 namestr = nsu_strsep(&cmdline, " \t\r\n");
1580 if (namestr == NULL || *namestr == 0) {
1581 fprintf(stderr, "could not read key name\n");
1582 return (STATUS_SYNTAX);
1583 }
1584
1585 mykeyname = dns_fixedname_initname(&fkeyname);
1586
1587 n = strchr(namestr, ':');
1588 if (n != NULL) {
1589 if (!parse_hmac(&hmacname, namestr, n - namestr,
1590 &digestbits)) {
1591 return (STATUS_SYNTAX);
1592 }
1593 namestr = n + 1;
1594 } else {
1595 hmacname = DNS_TSIG_HMACMD5_NAME;
1596 }
1597
1598 isc_buffer_init(&b, namestr, strlen(namestr));
1599 isc_buffer_add(&b, strlen(namestr));
1600 result = dns_name_fromtext(mykeyname, &b, dns_rootname, 0, NULL);
1601 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
1602 fprintf(stderr, "could not parse key name\n");
1603 return (STATUS_SYNTAX);
1604 }
1605
1606 secretstr = nsu_strsep(&cmdline, "\r\n");
1607 if (secretstr == NULL || *secretstr == 0) {
1608 fprintf(stderr, "could not read key secret\n");
1609 return (STATUS_SYNTAX);
1610 }
1611 secretlen = strlen(secretstr) * 3 / 4;
1612 secret = isc_mem_allocate(gmctx, secretlen);
1613 if (secret == NULL)
1614 fatal("out of memory");
1615
1616 isc_buffer_init(&secretbuf, secret, secretlen);
1617 result = isc_base64_decodestring(secretstr, &secretbuf);
1618 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
1619 fprintf(stderr, "could not create key from %s: %s\n",
1620 secretstr, isc_result_totext(result));
1621 isc_mem_free(gmctx, secret);
1622 return (STATUS_SYNTAX);
1623 }
1624 secretlen = isc_buffer_usedlength(&secretbuf);
1625
1626 if (tsigkey != NULL)
1627 dns_tsigkey_detach(&tsigkey);
1628 result = dns_tsigkey_create(mykeyname, hmacname, secret, secretlen,
1629 false, NULL, 0, 0, gmctx, NULL,
1630 &tsigkey);
1631 isc_mem_free(gmctx, secret);
1632 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
1633 fprintf(stderr, "could not create key from %s %s: %s\n",
1634 namestr, secretstr, dns_result_totext(result));
1635 return (STATUS_SYNTAX);
1636 }
1637 dst_key_setbits(tsigkey->key, digestbits);
1638 return (STATUS_MORE);
1639}

1763static uint16_t
1764update_addordelete(char *cmdline, bool isdelete) {
1765 isc_result_t result;
1766 dns_name_t *name = NULL;
1767 uint32_t ttl;
1768 char *word;
1769 dns_rdataclass_t rdataclass;
1770 dns_rdatatype_t rdatatype;
1771 dns_rdata_t *rdata = NULL;
1772 dns_rdatalist_t *rdatalist = NULL;
1773 dns_rdataset_t *rdataset = NULL;
1774 isc_textregion_t region;
1775 uint16_t retval;
1776
1777 ddebug("update_addordelete()");
1778
1779 /*
1780 * Read the owner name.
1781 */
1782 retval = parse_name(&cmdline, updatemsg, &name);
1783 if (retval != STATUS_MORE)
1784 return (retval);
1785
1786 result = dns_message_gettemprdata(updatemsg, &rdata);
1787 check_result(result, "dns_message_gettemprdata");
1788
1789 dns_rdata_init(rdata);
1790
1791 /*
1792 * If this is an add, read the TTL and verify that it's in range.
1793 * If it's a delete, ignore a TTL if present (for compatibility).
1794 */
1795 word = nsu_strsep(&cmdline, " \t\r\n");
1796 if (word == NULL || *word == 0) {
1797 if (!isdelete) {
1798 fprintf(stderr, "could not read owner ttl\n");
1799 goto failure;
1800 }
1801 else {
1802 ttl = 0;
1803 rdataclass = dns_rdataclass_any;
1804 rdatatype = dns_rdatatype_any;
1805 rdata->flags = DNS_RDATA_UPDATE;
1806 goto doneparsing;
1807 }
1808 }
1809 result = isc_parse_uint32(&ttl, word, 10);
1810 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
1811 if (isdelete) {
1812 ttl = 0;
1813 goto parseclass;
1814 } else if (default_ttl_set) {
1815 ttl = default_ttl;
1816 goto parseclass;
1817 } else {
1818 fprintf(stderr, "ttl '%s': %s\n", word,
1819 isc_result_totext(result));
1820 goto failure;
1821 }
1822 }
1823
1824 if (isdelete)
1825 ttl = 0;
1826 else if (ttl > TTL_MAX) {
1827 fprintf(stderr, "ttl '%s' is out of range (0 to %u)\n",
1828 word, TTL_MAX);
1829 goto failure;
1830 }
1831
1832 /*
1833 * Read the class or type.
1834 */
1835 word = nsu_strsep(&cmdline, " \t\r\n");
1836 parseclass:
1837 if (word == NULL || *word == 0) {
1838 if (isdelete) {
1839 rdataclass = dns_rdataclass_any;
1840 rdatatype = dns_rdatatype_any;
1841 rdata->flags = DNS_RDATA_UPDATE;
1842 goto doneparsing;
1843 } else {
1844 fprintf(stderr, "could not read class or type\n");
1845 goto failure;
1846 }
1847 }
1848 region.base = word;
1849 region.length = strlen(word);
1850 rdataclass = dns_rdataclass_any;
1851 result = dns_rdataclass_fromtext(&rdataclass, &region);
1852 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS && rdataclass != dns_rdataclass_any) {
1853 if (!setzoneclass(rdataclass)) {
1854 fprintf(stderr, "class mismatch: %s\n", word);
1855 goto failure;
1856 }
1857 /*
1858 * Now read the type.
1859 */
1860 word = nsu_strsep(&cmdline, " \t\r\n");
1861 if (word == NULL || *word == 0) {
1862 if (isdelete) {
1863 rdataclass = dns_rdataclass_any;
1864 rdatatype = dns_rdatatype_any;
1865 rdata->flags = DNS_RDATA_UPDATE;
1866 goto doneparsing;
1867 } else {
1868 fprintf(stderr, "could not read type\n");
1869 goto failure;
1870 }
1871 }
1872 region.base = word;
1873 region.length = strlen(word);
1874 result = dns_rdatatype_fromtext(&rdatatype, &region);
1875 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
1876 fprintf(stderr, "'%s' is not a valid type: %s\n",
1877 word, isc_result_totext(result));
1878 goto failure;
1879 }
1880 } else {
1881 rdataclass = getzoneclass();
1882 result = dns_rdatatype_fromtext(&rdatatype, &region);
1883 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
1884 fprintf(stderr, "'%s' is not a valid class or type: "
1885 "%s\n", word, isc_result_totext(result));
1886 goto failure;
1887 }
1888 }
1889
1890 retval = parse_rdata(&cmdline, rdataclass, rdatatype, updatemsg,
1891 rdata);
1892 if (retval != STATUS_MORE)
1893 goto failure;
1894
1895 if (isdelete) {
1896 if ((rdata->flags & DNS_RDATA_UPDATE) != 0)
1897 rdataclass = dns_rdataclass_any;
1898 else
1899 rdataclass = dns_rdataclass_none;
1900 } else {
1901 if ((rdata->flags & DNS_RDATA_UPDATE) != 0) {
1902 fprintf(stderr, "could not read rdata\n");
1903 goto failure;
1904 }
1905 }
1906
1907 if (!isdelete && checknames) {
1908 dns_fixedname_t fixed;
1909 dns_name_t *bad;
1910
1911 if (!dns_rdata_checkowner(name, rdata->rdclass, rdata->type,
1912 true))
1913 {
1914 char namebuf[DNS_NAME_FORMATSIZE];
1915
1916 dns_name_format(name, namebuf, sizeof(namebuf));
1917 fprintf(stderr, "check-names failed: bad owner '%s'\n",
1918 namebuf);
1919 goto failure;
1920 }
1921
1922 bad = dns_fixedname_initname(&fixed);
1923 if (!dns_rdata_checknames(rdata, name, bad)) {
1924 char namebuf[DNS_NAME_FORMATSIZE];
1925
1926 dns_name_format(bad, namebuf, sizeof(namebuf));
1927 fprintf(stderr, "check-names failed: bad name '%s'\n",
1928 namebuf);
1929 goto failure;
1930 }
1931 }
1932
1933 doneparsing:
1934
1935 result = dns_message_gettemprdatalist(updatemsg, &rdatalist);
1936 check_result(result, "dns_message_gettemprdatalist");
1937 result = dns_message_gettemprdataset(updatemsg, &rdataset);
1938 check_result(result, "dns_message_gettemprdataset");
1939 rdatalist->type = rdatatype;
1940 rdatalist->rdclass = rdataclass;
1941 rdatalist->covers = rdatatype;
1942 rdatalist->ttl = (dns_ttl_t)ttl;
1943 ISC_LIST_APPEND(rdatalist->rdata, rdata, link);
1944 dns_rdatalist_tordataset(rdatalist, rdataset);
1945 ISC_LIST_INIT(name->list);
1946 ISC_LIST_APPEND(name->list, rdataset, link);
1947 dns_message_addname(updatemsg, name, DNS_SECTION_UPDATE);
1948 return (STATUS_MORE);
1949
1950 failure:
1951 if (name != NULL)
1952 dns_message_puttempname(updatemsg, &name);
1953 dns_message_puttemprdata(updatemsg, &rdata);
1954 return (STATUS_SYNTAX);
1955}

1961
1962 ddebug("evaluate_update()");

2006static void
2007setzone(dns_name_t *zonename) {
2008 isc_result_t result;
2009 dns_name_t *name = NULL;
2010 dns_rdataset_t *rdataset = NULL;
2011
2012 result = dns_message_firstname(updatemsg, DNS_SECTION_ZONE);
2013 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
2014 dns_message_currentname(updatemsg, DNS_SECTION_ZONE, &name);
2015 dns_message_removename(updatemsg, name, DNS_SECTION_ZONE);
2016 for (rdataset = ISC_LIST_HEAD(name->list);
2017 rdataset != NULL;
2018 rdataset = ISC_LIST_HEAD(name->list)) {
2019 ISC_LIST_UNLINK(name->list, rdataset, link);
2020 dns_rdataset_disassociate(rdataset);
2021 dns_message_puttemprdataset(updatemsg, &rdataset);
2022 }
2023 dns_message_puttempname(updatemsg, &name);
2024 }
2025
2026 if (zonename != NULL) {

2194static uint16_t
2195get_next_command(void) {
2196 uint16_t result = STATUS_QUIT;
2197 char cmdlinebuf[MAXCMD];
2198 char *cmdline;
2199
2200 isc_app_block();
2201 if (interactive) {
2202#ifdef HAVE_READLINE
2203 cmdline = readline("> ");
2204 if (cmdline != NULL)
2205 add_history(cmdline);
2206#else
2207 fprintf(stdout, "> ");
2208 fflush(stdout);
2209 cmdline = fgets(cmdlinebuf, MAXCMD, input);
2210#endif
2211 } else
2212 cmdline = fgets(cmdlinebuf, MAXCMD, input);
2213 isc_app_unblock();
2214
2215 if (cmdline != NULL) {
2216 char *tmp = cmdline;
2217
2218 /*
2219 * Normalize input by removing any eol as readline()
2220 * removes eol but fgets doesn't.
2221 */
2222 (void)nsu_strsep(&tmp, "\r\n");
2223 result = do_next_command(cmdline);
2224 }
2225#ifdef HAVE_READLINE
2226 if (interactive)
2227 free(cmdline);
2228#endif
2229 return (result);
2230}

2291static void
2292update_completed(isc_task_t *task, isc_event_t *event) {
2293 dns_requestevent_t *reqev = NULL;
2294 isc_result_t result;
2295 dns_request_t *request;
2296
2297 UNUSED(task);
2298
2299 ddebug("update_completed()");
2300
2301 requests--;
2302
2303 REQUIRE(event->ev_type == DNS_EVENT_REQUESTDONE);
2304 reqev = (dns_requestevent_t *)event;
2305 request = reqev->request;
2306
2307 if (shuttingdown) {
2308 dns_request_destroy(&request);
2309 isc_event_free(&event);
2310 maybeshutdown();
2311 return;
2312 }
2313
2314 if (reqev->result != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
2315 if (!next_master("update_completed",
2316 &master_servers[master_inuse],
2317 reqev->result))
2318 {
2319 seenerror = true;
2320 goto done;
2321 }
2322
2323 ddebug("Destroying request [%p]", request);
2324 dns_request_destroy(&request);
2325 dns_message_renderreset(updatemsg);
2326 dns_message_settsigkey(updatemsg, NULL);
2327 send_update(zname, &master_servers[master_inuse]);
2328 isc_event_free(&event);
2329 return;
2330 }
2331
2332 result = dns_message_create(gmctx, DNS_MESSAGE_INTENTPARSE, &answer);
2333 check_result(result, "dns_message_create");
2334 result = dns_request_getresponse(request, answer,
2335 DNS_MESSAGEPARSE_PRESERVEORDER);
2336 switch (result) {
2337 case ISC_R_SUCCESS:
2338 if (answer->verify_attempted)
2339 ddebug("tsig verification successful");
2340 break;
2341 case DNS_R_CLOCKSKEW:
2342 case DNS_R_EXPECTEDTSIG:
2343 case DNS_R_TSIGERRORSET:
2344 case DNS_R_TSIGVERIFYFAILURE:
2345 case DNS_R_UNEXPECTEDTSIG:
2346 case ISC_R_FAILURE:
2347#if 0
2348 if (usegsstsig && answer->rcode == dns_rcode_noerror) {
2349 /*
2350 * For MS DNS that violates RFC 2845, section 4.2
2351 */
2352 break;
2353 }
2354#endif
2355 fprintf(stderr, "; TSIG error with server: %s\n",
2356 isc_result_totext(result));
2357 seenerror = true;
2358 break;
2359 default:
2360 check_result(result, "dns_request_getresponse");
2361 }
2362
2363 if (answer->rcode != dns_rcode_noerror) {
2364 seenerror = true;
2365 if (!debugging) {
2366 char buf[64];
2367 isc_buffer_t b;
2368 dns_rdataset_t *rds;
2369
2370 isc_buffer_init(&b, buf, sizeof(buf) - 1);
2371 result = dns_rcode_totext(answer->rcode, &b);
2372 check_result(result, "dns_rcode_totext");
2373 rds = dns_message_gettsig(answer, NULL);
2374 if (rds != NULL)
2375 check_tsig_error(rds, &b);
2376 fprintf(stderr, "update failed: %.*s\n",
2377 (int)isc_buffer_usedlength(&b), buf);
2378 }
2379 }
2380 if (debugging)
2381 show_message(stderr, answer, "\nReply from update query:");
2382
2383 done:
2384 dns_request_destroy(&request);
2385 if (usegsstsig) {
2386 dns_name_free(&tmpzonename, gmctx);
2387 dns_name_free(&restart_master, gmctx);
2388 dns_name_init(&tmpzonename, 0);
2389 dns_name_init(&restart_master, 0);
2390 }
2391 isc_event_free(&event);
2392 done_update();
2393}

2453static void
2454recvsoa(isc_task_t *task, isc_event_t *event) {
2455 dns_requestevent_t *reqev = NULL;
2456 dns_request_t *request = NULL;
2457 isc_result_t result, eresult;
2458 dns_message_t *rcvmsg = NULL;
2459 dns_section_t section;
2460 dns_name_t *name = NULL;
2461 dns_rdataset_t *soaset = NULL;
2462 dns_rdata_soa_t soa;
2463 dns_rdata_t soarr = DNS_RDATA_INIT;
2464 int pass = 0;
2465 dns_name_t master;
2466 nsu_requestinfo_t *reqinfo;
2467 dns_message_t *soaquery = NULL;
2468 isc_sockaddr_t *addr;
2469 isc_sockaddr_t *srcaddr;
2470 bool seencname = false;
2471 dns_name_t tname;
2472 unsigned int nlabels;
2473
2474 UNUSED(task);
2475
2476 ddebug("recvsoa()");
2477
2478 requests--;
2479
2480 REQUIRE(event->ev_type == DNS_EVENT_REQUESTDONE);
2481 reqev = (dns_requestevent_t *)event;
2482 request = reqev->request;
2483 eresult = reqev->result;
2484 reqinfo = reqev->ev_arg;
2485 soaquery = reqinfo->msg;
2486 addr = reqinfo->addr;
2487
2488 if (shuttingdown) {
2489 dns_request_destroy(&request);
2490 dns_message_destroy(&soaquery);
2491 isc_mem_put(gmctx, reqinfo, sizeof(nsu_requestinfo_t));
2492 isc_event_free(&event);
2493 maybeshutdown();
2494 return;
2495 }
2496
2497 if (eresult != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
2498 next_server("recvsoa", addr, eresult);
2499 ddebug("Destroying request [%p]", request);
2500 dns_request_destroy(&request);
2501 dns_message_renderreset(soaquery);
2502 dns_message_settsigkey(soaquery, NULL);
2503 sendrequest(&servers[ns_inuse], soaquery, &request);
2504 isc_mem_put(gmctx, reqinfo, sizeof(nsu_requestinfo_t));
2505 isc_event_free(&event);
2506 setzoneclass(dns_rdataclass_none);
2507 return;
2508 }
2509
2510 isc_mem_put(gmctx, reqinfo, sizeof(nsu_requestinfo_t));
2511 reqinfo = NULL;
2512 isc_event_free(&event);
2513 reqev = NULL;
2514
2515 ddebug("About to create rcvmsg");
2516 result = dns_message_create(gmctx, DNS_MESSAGE_INTENTPARSE, &rcvmsg);
2517 check_result(result, "dns_message_create");
2518 result = dns_request_getresponse(request, rcvmsg,
2519 DNS_MESSAGEPARSE_PRESERVEORDER);
2520 if (result == DNS_R_TSIGERRORSET && servers != NULL) {
2521 dns_message_destroy(&rcvmsg);
2522 ddebug("Destroying request [%p]", request);
2523 dns_request_destroy(&request);
2524 reqinfo = isc_mem_get(gmctx, sizeof(nsu_requestinfo_t));
2525 if (reqinfo == NULL)
2526 fatal("out of memory");
2527 reqinfo->msg = soaquery;
2528 reqinfo->addr = addr;
2529 dns_message_renderreset(soaquery);
2530 ddebug("retrying soa request without TSIG");
2531
2532 if (isc_sockaddr_pf(addr) == AF_INET6)
2533 srcaddr = localaddr6;
2534 else
2535 srcaddr = localaddr4;
2536
2537 result = dns_request_createvia(requestmgr, soaquery, srcaddr,
2538 addr, -1, 0, NULL,
2539 FIND_TIMEOUT * 20,
2540 FIND_TIMEOUT, 3,
2541 global_task, recvsoa, reqinfo,
2542 &request);
2543 check_result(result, "dns_request_createvia");
2544 requests++;
2545 return;
2546 }
2547 check_result(result, "dns_request_getresponse");
2548 section = DNS_SECTION_ANSWER;
2549 POST(section);
2550 if (debugging)
2551 show_message(stderr, rcvmsg, "Reply from SOA query:");
2552
2553 if (rcvmsg->rcode != dns_rcode_noerror &&
2554 rcvmsg->rcode != dns_rcode_nxdomain)
2555 fatal("response to SOA query was unsuccessful");
2556
2557 if (userzone != NULL && rcvmsg->rcode == dns_rcode_nxdomain) {
2558 char namebuf[DNS_NAME_FORMATSIZE];
2559 dns_name_format(userzone, namebuf, sizeof(namebuf));
2560 error("specified zone '%s' does not exist (NXDOMAIN)",
2561 namebuf);
2562 dns_message_destroy(&rcvmsg);
2563 dns_request_destroy(&request);
2564 dns_message_destroy(&soaquery);
2565 ddebug("Out of recvsoa");
2566 done_update();
2567 seenerror = true;
2568 return;
2569 }
2570
2571 lookforsoa:
2572 if (pass == 0)
2573 section = DNS_SECTION_ANSWER;
2574 else if (pass == 1)
2575 section = DNS_SECTION_AUTHORITY;
2576 else
2577 goto droplabel;
2578
2579 result = dns_message_firstname(rcvmsg, section);
2580 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
2581 pass++;
2582 goto lookforsoa;
2583 }
2584 while (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
2585 name = NULL;
2586 dns_message_currentname(rcvmsg, section, &name);
2587 soaset = NULL;
2588 result = dns_message_findtype(name, dns_rdatatype_soa, 0,
2589 &soaset);
2590 if (result == ISC_R_SUCCESS)
2591 break;
2592 if (section == DNS_SECTION_ANSWER) {
2593 dns_rdataset_t *tset = NULL;
2594 if (dns_message_findtype(name, dns_rdatatype_cname, 0,
2595 &tset) == ISC_R_SUCCESS ||
2596 dns_message_findtype(name, dns_rdatatype_dname, 0,
2597 &tset) == ISC_R_SUCCESS ) {
2598 seencname = true;
2599 break;
2600 }
2601 }
2602
2603 result = dns_message_nextname(rcvmsg, section);
2604 }
2605
2606 if (soaset == NULL && !seencname) {
2607 pass++;
2608 goto lookforsoa;
2609 }
2610
2611 if (seencname)
2612 goto droplabel;
2613
2614 if (debugging) {
2615 char namestr[DNS_NAME_FORMATSIZE];
2616 dns_name_format(name, namestr, sizeof(namestr));
2617 fprintf(stderr, "Found zone name: %s\n", namestr);
2618 }
2619
2620 result = dns_rdataset_first(soaset);
2621 check_result(result, "dns_rdataset_first");
2622
2623 dns_rdata_init(&soarr);
2624 dns_rdataset_current(soaset, &soarr);
2625 result = dns_rdata_tostruct(&soarr, &soa, NULL);
2626 check_result(result, "dns_rdata_tostruct");
2627
2628 dns_name_init(&master, NULL);
2629 dns_name_clone(&soa.origin, &master);
2630
2631 if (userzone != NULL) {
2632 zname = userzone;
2633 } else {
2634 /*
2635 * Save the zone name in case we need to try a second
2636 * address.
2637 */
2638 zname = dns_fixedname_initname(&fzname);
2639 dns_name_copy(name, zname, NULL);
2640 }
2641
2642 if (debugging) {
2643 char namestr[DNS_NAME_FORMATSIZE];
2644 dns_name_format(&master, namestr, sizeof(namestr));
2645 fprintf(stderr, "The master is: %s\n", namestr);
2646 }
2647
2648 if (default_servers) {
2649 char serverstr[DNS_NAME_MAXTEXT+1];
2650 isc_buffer_t buf;
2651 size_t size;
2652
2653 isc_buffer_init(&buf, serverstr, sizeof(serverstr));
2654 result = dns_name_totext(&master, true, &buf);
2655 check_result(result, "dns_name_totext");
2656 serverstr[isc_buffer_usedlength(&buf)] = 0;
2657
2658 if (master_servers != NULL && master_servers != servers)
2659 isc_mem_put(gmctx, master_servers,
2660 master_alloc * sizeof(isc_sockaddr_t));
2661 master_alloc = MAX_SERVERADDRS;
2662 size = master_alloc * sizeof(isc_sockaddr_t);
2663 master_servers = isc_mem_get(gmctx, size);
2664 if (master_servers == NULL)
2665 fatal("out of memory");
2666
2667 memset(master_servers, 0, size);
2668 master_total = get_addresses(serverstr, dnsport,
2669 master_servers, master_alloc);
2670 if (master_total == 0) {
2671 exit(1);
2672 }
2673 master_inuse = 0;
2674 } else
2675 master_from_servers();
2676 dns_rdata_freestruct(&soa);
2677
2678#ifdef GSSAPI
2679 if (usegsstsig) {
2680 dns_name_init(&tmpzonename, NULL);
2681 dns_name_dup(zname, gmctx, &tmpzonename);
2682 dns_name_init(&restart_master, NULL);
2683 dns_name_dup(&master, gmctx, &restart_master);
2684 start_gssrequest(&master);
2685 } else {
2686 send_update(zname, &master_servers[master_inuse]);
2687 setzoneclass(dns_rdataclass_none);
2688 }
2689#else
2690 send_update(zname, &master_servers[master_inuse]);
2691 setzoneclass(dns_rdataclass_none);
2692#endif
2693
2694 dns_message_destroy(&soaquery);
2695 dns_request_destroy(&request);
2696
2697 out:
2698 dns_message_destroy(&rcvmsg);
2699 ddebug("Out of recvsoa");
2700 return;
2701
2702 droplabel:
2703 result = dns_message_firstname(soaquery, DNS_SECTION_QUESTION);
2704 INSIST(result == ISC_R_SUCCESS);
2705 name = NULL;
2706 dns_message_currentname(soaquery, DNS_SECTION_QUESTION, &name);
2707 nlabels = dns_name_countlabels(name);
2708 if (nlabels == 1)
2709 fatal("could not find enclosing zone");
2710 dns_name_init(&tname, NULL);
2711 dns_name_getlabelsequence(name, 1, nlabels - 1, &tname);
2712 dns_name_clone(&tname, name);
2713 dns_request_destroy(&request);
2714 dns_message_renderreset(soaquery);
2715 dns_message_settsigkey(soaquery, NULL);
2716 sendrequest(&servers[ns_inuse], soaquery, &request);
2717 goto out;
2718}

2749/*
2750 * Get the realm from the users kerberos ticket if possible
2751 */
2752static void
2753get_ticket_realm(isc_mem_t *mctx) {
2754 krb5_context ctx;
2755 krb5_error_code rc;
2756 krb5_ccache ccache;
2757 krb5_principal princ;
2758 char *name;
2759 const char * ticket_realm;
2760
2761 rc = krb5_init_context(&ctx);
2762 if (rc != 0)
2763 return;
2764
2765 rc = krb5_cc_default(ctx, &ccache);
2766 if (rc != 0) {
2767 krb5_free_context(ctx);
2768 return;
2769 }
2770
2771 rc = krb5_cc_get_principal(ctx, ccache, &princ);
2772 if (rc != 0) {
2773 krb5_cc_close(ctx, ccache);
2774 krb5_free_context(ctx);
2775 return;
2776 }
2777
2778 rc = krb5_unparse_name(ctx, princ, &name);
2779 if (rc != 0) {
2780 krb5_free_principal(ctx, princ);
2781 krb5_cc_close(ctx, ccache);
2782 krb5_free_context(ctx);
2783 return;
2784 }
2785
2786 ticket_realm = strrchr(name, '@');
2787 if (ticket_realm != NULL) {
2788 realm = isc_mem_strdup(mctx, ticket_realm);
2789 }
2790
2791 free(name);
2792 krb5_free_principal(ctx, princ);
2793 krb5_cc_close(ctx, ccache);
2794 krb5_free_context(ctx);
2795 if (realm != NULL && debugging)
2796 fprintf(stderr, "Found realm from ticket: %s\n", realm+1);
2797}

2811static void
2812start_gssrequest(dns_name_t *master) {

2814 isc_buffer_t buf;
2815 isc_result_t result;
2816 uint32_t val = 0;
2817 dns_message_t *rmsg = NULL;
2818 dns_request_t *request = NULL;
2819 dns_name_t *servname;
2820 dns_fixedname_t fname;
2821 char namestr[DNS_NAME_FORMATSIZE];
2822 char mykeystr[DNS_NAME_FORMATSIZE];
2823 char *err_message = NULL;
2824
2825 debug("start_gssrequest");
2826 usevc = true;
2827
2828 if (gssring != NULL)
2829 dns_tsigkeyring_detach(&gssring);
2830 gssring = NULL;
2831 result = dns_tsigkeyring_create(gmctx, &gssring);
2832
2833 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
2834 fatal("dns_tsigkeyring_create failed: %s",
2835 isc_result_totext(result));
2836
2837 dns_name_format(master, namestr, sizeof(namestr));
2838 if (kserver == NULL) {
2839 kserver = isc_mem_get(gmctx, sizeof(isc_sockaddr_t));
2840 if (kserver == NULL)
2841 fatal("out of memory");
2842 }
2843
2844 memmove(kserver, &master_servers[master_inuse],
2845 sizeof(isc_sockaddr_t));
2846
2847 servname = dns_fixedname_initname(&fname);
2848
2849 if (realm == NULL)
2850 get_ticket_realm(gmctx);
2851
2852 result = snprintf(servicename, sizeof(servicename), "DNS/%s%s",
2853 namestr, realm ? realm : "");
2854 RUNTIME_CHECK(result < sizeof(servicename));
2855 isc_buffer_init(&buf, servicename, strlen(servicename));
2856 isc_buffer_add(&buf, strlen(servicename));
2857 result = dns_name_fromtext(servname, &buf, dns_rootname, 0, NULL);
2858 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
2859 fatal("dns_name_fromtext(servname) failed: %s",
2860 isc_result_totext(result));
2861 }
2862
2863 keyname = dns_fixedname_initname(&fkname);
2864
2865 isc_nonce_buf(&val, sizeof(val));
2866
2867 result = snprintf(mykeystr, sizeof(mykeystr), "%u.sig-%s", val,
2868 namestr);
2869 RUNTIME_CHECK(result <= sizeof(mykeystr));
2870
2871 isc_buffer_init(&buf, mykeystr, strlen(mykeystr));
2872 isc_buffer_add(&buf, strlen(mykeystr));
2873
2874 result = dns_name_fromtext(keyname, &buf, dns_rootname, 0, NULL);
2875 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
2876 fatal("dns_name_fromtext(keyname) failed: %s",
2877 isc_result_totext(result));
2878 }
2879
2880 /* Windows doesn't recognize name compression in the key name. */
2881 keyname->attributes |= DNS_NAMEATTR_NOCOMPRESS;
2882
2883 rmsg = NULL;
2884 result = dns_message_create(gmctx, DNS_MESSAGE_INTENTRENDER, &rmsg);
2885 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
2886 fatal("dns_message_create failed: %s",
2887 isc_result_totext(result));
2888
2889 /* Build first request. */
2890 context = GSS_C_NO_CONTEXT;
2891 result = dns_tkey_buildgssquery(rmsg, keyname, servname, NULL, 0,
2892 &context, use_win2k_gsstsig,
2893 gmctx, &err_message);
2894 if (result == ISC_R_FAILURE) {
2895 fprintf(stderr, "tkey query failed: %s\n",
2896 err_message != NULL ? err_message : "unknown error");

2898 }
2899 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS)
2900 fatal("dns_tkey_buildgssquery failed: %s",
2901 isc_result_totext(result));

2903 send_gssrequest(kserver, rmsg, &request, context);
2904 return;

3105static void
3106start_update(void) {
3107 isc_result_t result;
3108 dns_rdataset_t *rdataset = NULL;
3109 dns_name_t *name = NULL;
3110 dns_request_t *request = NULL;
3111 dns_message_t *soaquery = NULL;
3112 dns_name_t *firstname;
3113 dns_section_t section = DNS_SECTION_UPDATE;
3114
3115 ddebug("start_update()");
3116
3117 if (answer != NULL)
3118 dns_message_destroy(&answer);
3119
3120 /*
3121 * If we have both the zone and the servers we have enough information
3122 * to send the update straight away otherwise we need to discover
3123 * the zone and / or the master server.
3124 */
3125 if (userzone != NULL && !default_servers && !usegsstsig) {
3126 master_from_servers();
3127 send_update(userzone, &master_servers[master_inuse]);
3128 setzoneclass(dns_rdataclass_none);
3129 return;
3130 }
3131
3132 result = dns_message_create(gmctx, DNS_MESSAGE_INTENTRENDER,
3133 &soaquery);
3134 check_result(result, "dns_message_create");
3135
3136 if (default_servers)
3137 soaquery->flags |= DNS_MESSAGEFLAG_RD;
3138
3139 result = dns_message_gettempname(soaquery, &name);
3140 check_result(result, "dns_message_gettempname");
3141
3142 result = dns_message_gettemprdataset(soaquery, &rdataset);
3143 check_result(result, "dns_message_gettemprdataset");
3144
3145 dns_rdataset_makequestion(rdataset, getzoneclass(), dns_rdatatype_soa);
3146
3147 if (userzone != NULL) {
3148 dns_name_init(name, NULL);
3149 dns_name_clone(userzone, name);
3150 } else {
3151 dns_rdataset_t *tmprdataset;
3152 result = dns_message_firstname(updatemsg, section);
3153 if (result == ISC_R_NOMORE) {
3154 section = DNS_SECTION_PREREQUISITE;
3155 result = dns_message_firstname(updatemsg, section);
3156 }
3157 if (result != ISC_R_SUCCESS) {
3158 dns_message_puttempname(soaquery, &name);
3159 dns_rdataset_disassociate(rdataset);
3160 dns_message_puttemprdataset(soaquery, &rdataset);
3161 dns_message_destroy(&soaquery);
3162 done_update();
3163 return;
3164 }
3165 firstname = NULL;
3166 dns_message_currentname(updatemsg, section, &firstname);
3167 dns_name_init(name, NULL);
3168 dns_name_clone(firstname, name);
3169 /*
3170 * Looks to see if the first name references a DS record
3171 * and if that name is not the root remove a label as DS
3172 * records live in the parent zone so we need to start our
3173 * search one label up.
3174 */
3175 tmprdataset = ISC_LIST_HEAD(firstname->list);
3176 if (section == DNS_SECTION_UPDATE &&
3177 !dns_name_equal(firstname, dns_rootname) &&
3178 tmprdataset->type == dns_rdatatype_ds) {
3179 unsigned int labels = dns_name_countlabels(name);
3180 dns_name_getlabelsequence(name, 1, labels - 1, name);
3181 }
3182 }
3183
3184 ISC_LIST_INIT(name->list);
3185 ISC_LIST_APPEND(name->list, rdataset, link);
3186 dns_message_addname(soaquery, name, DNS_SECTION_QUESTION);
3187
3188 ns_inuse = 0;
3189 sendrequest(&servers[ns_inuse], soaquery, &request);
3190}
